The Agbado Community Landlord Association in Ifo Local Government of Ogun State has praised the Agbado Police Command over the ongoing renovation of the station. Speaking to Daily Independent recently, one its leaders, Chief Samson Adeyemo, said the ongoing renovation would add to the beautification of the station thereby making the police officers to perform their lawful duties to the members of the public. This commendation also goes to the Divisional Police Officer, Superintendent of Police, SP Adekunle Awoniyi, and S.O. Hassan Kehinde including other officers in the station. Chief Adeyemo also extended commendation to all those involved in the ongoing renovation such as community, spirited organisations and police authorities. He, therefore, appealed to Agbado Community to work hand in hand with the officers to stem the activities of hoodlums, area boys and other undesirable elements in the society.